The paper deals with optimization guarantees, generalization bounds, and statistical consistency results for AdaBoost variants, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of the logistic loss as a replacement for the exponential loss in AdaBoost, which is a popular boosting algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are also relevant to the topic. Additionally, since the paper deals with image classification tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper provides statistical guarantees, cs.ST (Statistics) is also a possible sub-category.
